-- South African Yellow Corn Declines for First Time in 12 Days
-- B y   T s h e p i s o   M o k h e m a
-- 2013-10-29T13:23:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-29/south-african-yellow-corn-declines-for-first-time-in-12-days.html
South African yellow corn futures
fell, snapping an 11-day streak of advances, by the midday close
in Johannesburg. White corn dropped.  Yellow corn for delivery in December, the most active
contract, declined 1 percent to 2,253 rand ($228) a metric ton,
the first drop since Oct. 11 on the South African Futures
Exchange. The white variety for delivery in the same month
retreated 1 percent to 2,375 rand a ton.  The nation is  Africa â€™s biggest producer of the grain.
Yellow corn is mainly used as  animal feed , while the white
variety is a staple food in the country.  Wheat for delivery in December fell 0.1 percent to 3,485
rand a ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
